{
  "stem": "11067.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But my mother insisted and said, let's at least save one member of the family, because things are not going to be-- get any better.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so when a very short time, it had to be within a couple of weeks, that I was on my way.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, how was I on my way?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Possibly-- first of all, there had to be an exchange of money.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How much, I cannot tell you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But of course, Kindertransport was an agreement between Germany and Britain, that Britain would take in 10,000 unaccompanied children.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a suitcase packed in our house, which was actually for my sister Edith.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My sister Edith was supposed to have come to Cincinnati, Ohio.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a family who was going to take her in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we never heard.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, of course, the State Department in the United States was isolationist at that time and canceled the acceptance of 20,000 children from Germany to America.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we have reason to believe that my sister Edith was one of those.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that suitcase had been packed for Edith to come to America.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And now, it became my suitcase.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was going to England with me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The clothes in it were clothes that had come from a department store that had been owned by my mother's aunt and uncle that had been taken over by the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But before that was done, they managed to take some stuff out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And clothes, as I said, were given to us and also to my cousins, both in the town in Frankfurt and then in the town of [NON-ENGLISH] in Holland.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so on July 25, 1939, I left for England.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My mother and I left on a train from Duisburg to go to Worms at 5 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
